  <h2>The General Steps</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Truck positioning.</strong> The provider parks within hose reach of the tank.</li>
    <li><strong>Locating and opening.</strong> The tank is found (if needed) and the lids are opened.</li>
    <li><strong>Pumping.</strong> Liquid and settled solids are removed from each compartment.</li>
    <li><strong>A look at condition.</strong> The provider can observe sludge levels, baffles and obvious concerns.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How to Prepare — and What to Ask</h2>
  <p>
    Clear a path for the truck, make sure the lids are accessible, and know roughly where the tank is. Afterward, ask how full the tank was and what that suggests for your <a href="/how-often-to-pump-septic-tank/">pumping interval</a>. When you are ready, <a href="/request-service/">request septic service</a>.
  </p>

